<Layout title="Econ Ch.14 — Information Asymmetry" favicon="💰">
  <main>

    <a href="/reading/economics/" class="text-sm mb-4 inline-block">← back to economics</a>

    <h1>Information Asymmetry</h1>
    <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mb-6">George Akerlof · 1970 / Michael Spence · 1973 · <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Information_asymmetry"><img src="/reading/wikipedia.svg" alt="wp" style="display:inline;height:1em;vertical-align:-0.1em;margin-right:0.2em;"/>Wikipedia: Information asymmetry</a></p>

    <div class="bg-zinc-800 rounded-lg p-5 mb-8 callout">
      <p class="text-lg" style="max-width:none"><strong>Information asymmetry</strong> means one side of a transaction knows more than the other. Sellers know their car's history. Employees know their own effort level. Insurees know their own risk. This imbalance causes markets to malfunction: good products get driven out, risky people get insured, and effort drops when unobserved.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- 1. Akerlof's lemons -->
    <h3>The market for lemons</h3>
    <p>Akerlof's 1970 insight: if buyers can't distinguish good used cars from bad ones ("lemons"), they offer an average price. Sellers of good cars find this too low and withdraw. The average quality drops, so the price drops further. In the worst case, only lemons remain. Bad quality drives out good: adverse selection.</p>

    <!-- SVG: Market with hidden quality gradient -->
    <div class="flex justify-center my-6">
      <svg viewBox="0 0 400 240" class="w-full max-w-md" style="font-family: ui-monospace, monospace;">
        <!-- Quality gradient bar -->
        <text x="200" y="25" text-anchor="middle" fill="currentColor" font-size="13" fill-opacity="0.7">Car Quality (hidden from buyer)</text>

        <!-- Cars as rectangles with gradient -->
        <rect x="40" y="40" width="40" height="30" rx="3" fill="#a1a1aa" fill-opacity="0.15" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1" opacity="0.4"/>
        <text x="60" y="60" text-anchor="middle" fill="currentColor" font-size="9" fill-opacity="0.4">Lemon</text>

        <rect x="100" y="40" width="40" height="30" rx="3" fill="#a1a1aa" fill-opacity="0.18" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1" opacity="0.4"/>
        <rect x="160" y="40" width="40" height="30" rx="3" fill="currentColor" fill-opacity="0.22" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1" opacity="0.4"/>
        <rect x="220" y="40" width="40" height="30" rx="3" fill="currentColor" fill-opacity="0.30" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1" opacity="0.4"/>
        <rect x="280" y="40" width="40" height="30" rx="3" fill="currentColor" fill-opacity="0.38" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1" opacity="0.4"/>

